Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery vessel, possibly a krater or a dinos; interior: reserved; exterior: dark grey slip; decoration in relief consisting of tendril and dot.
Curator's comments: The fabric and decorative techniques find parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.644.c. This sherd was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The origin of the fabric (NAUK 47) was not identified and considered a chemical singleton.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.123)
